<subSubSection pageNumber="721" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="721">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="721">Note:</emphasis>
Chase (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="721">Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb.</emphasis>
22: 216. 1920) used the name in the sense of pearl millet but did not explicitly designate a type. There is also discussion of the name and its usage by Stapf (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="721">Kew Bull.</emphasis>
1928: 147-149. 1928) and Terrell (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="721">Taxon</emphasis>
25: 297-304. 1976). Rauschert, however, appears to have been the first to make an unequivocal choice of type.
</paragraph>
